{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b750ee4-c6b7-48b0-b2f5-4fecfcb6e076","content":"For a web API with authentication, use the **ASP.NET Core Web API** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API style (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` for the full list of options for your installed SDK version. Would you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6a271430-44a9-4f29-a24c-053d9fc14cb5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the current working directory or if this is just a general knowledge question.\n\nLet me look at what's in the current directory first to see if there's context about templates.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"93D0:162674:A19494:BAD778:69F2A76C"},"id":"9d99e089-0e3f-4edd-96b5-205feb855893","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:00.299Z","parentId":"7b59a1e9-a2f9-4261-9eae-d8eedfcef198"}
